article.headline: Delaware State 59, Wagner 48
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Terrance Hunter scored 17 points and Delaware State led all the way in a 59-48 victory over Wagner on Tuesday night. Jahsha Bluntt had 11 points for the Hornets (1-2), who led 28-22 at halftime. Nigel Wyatt had 16 points for the Seahawks (0-3), while Teoine Carroll added 14 and Sean Munson had 10 points and 11 rebounds. A 3-pointer by Miles Davis capped the Hornets' 7-0 run to open the game. The Seahawks were within 51-48 on a jumper by Wyatt with 2:12 left, but the Hornets scored the final eight points of the game, six by Hunter, to seal the win.
